<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Table Formatting on Crest — Command-Line API for Java</title><link>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/</link><description>Recent content in Table Formatting on Crest — Command-Line API for Java</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>The @Table Annotation</title><link>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/table-annotation/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/table-annotation/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;@Table&lt;/code&gt; annotation transforms collection-based return types into formatted tabular output. It works on commands that return &lt;code&gt;Stream&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;List&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;Set&lt;/code&gt;, or arrays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="basic-usage"&gt;Basic Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Place &lt;code&gt;@Table&lt;/code&gt; on a &lt;code&gt;@Command&lt;/code&gt; method alongside the return type:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;@Command&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;@Table&lt;/span&gt;(fields&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff"&gt;&amp;#34;id name version&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;sort&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;border&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Border.unicodeSingle)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;List&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Package&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;list&lt;/span&gt;()&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;packageService.findAll();&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The framework uses reflection to extract values from each element in the returned collection, building rows from the specified fields.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Border Styles</title><link>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/border-styles/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/border-styles/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Crest provides 15 border styles through the &lt;code&gt;Border&lt;/code&gt; enum. The default is &lt;code&gt;asciiCompact&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="available-styles"&gt;Available Styles&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
 &lt;thead&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Enum Value&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/thead&gt;
 &lt;tbody&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;asciiCompact&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Compact ASCII borders (default)&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;asciiDots&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Dotted ASCII borders&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;asciiSeparated&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;ASCII with row separators&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;githubMarkdown&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;GitHub-flavored Markdown table&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;mysqlStyle&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;MySQL client output style&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;unicodeDouble&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Double-line Unicode box drawing&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;unicodeSingle&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Single-line Unicode box drawing&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;unicodeSingleSeparated&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Single-line Unicode with row separators&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;whitespaceCompact&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Compact whitespace-only alignment&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;whitespaceSeparated&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Whitespace with blank line separators&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;tsv&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Tab-separated values&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;csv&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Comma-separated values&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;reStructuredTextGrid&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;reStructuredText grid table&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;reStructuredTextSimple&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;reStructuredText simple table&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;tr&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;&lt;code&gt;redditMarkdown&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;td&gt;Reddit-flavored Markdown table&lt;/td&gt;
 &lt;/tr&gt;
 &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;h2 id="example-output"&gt;Example Output&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Given a table with columns &lt;code&gt;name&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;version&lt;/code&gt;, and &lt;code&gt;status&lt;/code&gt;, here is how several popular styles render.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Table Options</title><link>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/table-options/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/table-options/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;TableOptions&lt;/code&gt; parameter allows end users to override table formatting settings at runtime via CLI flags. Add it as a parameter to any &lt;code&gt;@Table&lt;/code&gt;-annotated command.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="adding-tableoptions-to-a-command"&gt;Adding TableOptions to a Command&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Include &lt;code&gt;TableOptions&lt;/code&gt; as a parameter in your command method. No annotation is needed &amp;ndash; Crest recognizes it automatically:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;@Command&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;@Table&lt;/span&gt;(fields&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff"&gt;&amp;#34;name state schedule&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;sort&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Stream&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Job&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;list&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Config&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;config,&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;TableOptions&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;tableOptions)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;jobService.stream(config);&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;@Table&lt;/code&gt; annotation defines the defaults. When the user provides CLI flags, &lt;code&gt;TableOptions&lt;/code&gt; captures those overrides and the framework applies them on top of the annotation values.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Programmatic Table Building</title><link>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/programmatic/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/programmatic/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;When you need more control than the &lt;code&gt;@Table&lt;/code&gt; annotation provides, use &lt;code&gt;TableOutput.builder()&lt;/code&gt; to construct table output programmatically. &lt;code&gt;TableOutput&lt;/code&gt; implements &lt;code&gt;PrintOutput&lt;/code&gt;, so it can be returned directly from a command method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="basic-usage"&gt;Basic Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#e6edf3;background-color:#0d1117;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-java" data-lang="java"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;@Command&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;TableOutput&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#d2a8ff;font-weight:bold"&gt;report&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;Config&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;config)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;{&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;final&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;List&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Account&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;accounts&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72;font-weight:bold"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;loadAccounts(config);&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ff7b72"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;TableOutput.builder()&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;.data(accounts)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;.fields(&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff"&gt;&amp;#34;id name email status&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;.sort(&lt;span style="color:#a5d6ff"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;.border(Border.asciiCompact)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;.header(&lt;span style="color:#79c0ff"&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;.build();&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&lt;span style="color:#6e7681"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="builder-methods"&gt;Builder Methods&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="data"&gt;data()&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sets the data source for the table. Accepts multiple input types:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Cell Formatting</title><link>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/cell-formatting/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://tomitribe.github.io/crest/tables/cell-formatting/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Crest uses Java&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;PropertyEditor&lt;/code&gt; mechanism to format individual table cells. This allows you to control the display representation of any type that appears in your table output.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-cell-rendering-works"&gt;How Cell Rendering Works&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When rendering a cell value, the framework follows this resolution order:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PropertyEditor lookup&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; if a &lt;code&gt;PropertyEditor&lt;/code&gt; is registered for the field&amp;rsquo;s type and it implements &lt;code&gt;getAsText()&lt;/code&gt;, that result is used.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;toString() fallback&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; if no editor is found, the cell value&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;toString()&lt;/code&gt; method is called.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This means any &lt;code&gt;@Editor&lt;/code&gt; you register for CLI argument parsing will also control how that type appears in table cells, provided it implements &lt;code&gt;getAsText()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>